1.name: GPSLatitudeRef
1.desc: Indicates whether the latitude is north or south latitude.

3.name: GPSLongitudeRef
3.desc: Indicates whether the longitude is east or west longitude.

5.name: GPSAltitudeRef
5.desc: Indicates the altitude used as the reference altitude.

6.name: GPSAltitude
6.desc: Indicates the altitude based on the reference in GPSAltitudeRef.

7.name: GPSTimeStamp
7.desc: Indicates the time as UTC (Coordinated Universal Time).

8.name: GPSSatellites
8.desc: Indicates the GPS satellites used for measurements.

9.name: GPSStatus
9.desc: Indicates the status of the GPS receiver when the image is recorded.

11.name: GPSDOP
11.desc: Indicates the GPS DOP (data degree of precision).

12.name: GPSSpeedRef
12.desc: Indicates the unit used to express the GPS receiver speed of movement.

13.name: GPSSpeed
13.desc: Indicates the speed of GPS receiver movement.

14.name: GPSTrackRef
14.desc: Indicates the reference for giving the direction of GPS receiver movement.

15.name: GPSTrack
15.desc: Indicates the direction of GPS receiver movement.

16.name: GPSImgDirectionRef
16.desc: Indicates the reference for giving the direction of the image when it is captured.

17.name: GPSImgDirection
17.desc: Indicates the direction of the image when it was captured.

18.name: GPSMapDatum
18.desc: Indicates the geodetic survey data used by the GPS receiver.

19.name: GPSDestLatitudeRef
19.desc: Indicates whether the latitude of the destination point is north or south latitude.

20.name: GPSDestLatitude
20.desc: Indicates the latitude of the destination point.

21.name: GPSDestLongitudeRef
21.desc: Indicates whether the longitude of the destination point is east or west longitude.

22.name: GPSDestLongitude
22.desc: Indicates the longitude of the destination point.

23.name: GPSDestBearingRef
23.desc: Indicates the reference used for giving the bearing to the destination point.

24.name: GPSDestBearing
24.desc: Indicates the bearing to the destination point.

25.name: GPSDestDistanceRef
25.desc: Indicates the unit used to express the distance to the destination point.

26.name: GPSDestDistance
26.desc: Indicates the distance to the destination point.

27.name: GPSProcessingMethod
27.desc: A character string recording the name of the method used for location finding.

28.name: GPSAreaInformation
28.desc: A character string recording the name of the GPS area.

29.name: GPSDateStamp
29.desc: A character string recording date and time information relative to UTC (Coordinated Universal Time).

30.name: GPSDifferential
30.desc: Indicates whether differential correction is applied to the GPS receiver.

254.name: NewSubfileType
254.desc: A general indication of the kind of data contained in this subfile.

255.name: SubfileType
255.desc: A general indication of the kind of data contained in this subfile.

256.name: ImageWidth
256.desc: The number of columns in the image, i.e., the number of pixels per row.

257.name: ImageLength
257.desc: The number of rows of pixels in the image.

259.name: Compression
259.desc: Compression scheme used on the image data.

262.name: PhotometricInterpretation
262.desc: The color space of the image data.

263.name: Threshholding
263.desc: For black and white TIFF files that represent shades of gray, the technique used to convert from gray to black and white pixels.

264.name: CellWidth
264.short_desc: The width of the dithering or halftoning matrix used to create a dithered or halftoned bilevel file.
264.desc: The width of the dithering or halftoning matrix used to create a dithered or halftoned bilevel file.

265.name: CellLength
265.short_desc: The length of the dithering or halftoning matrix used to create a dithered or halftoned bilevel file.
265.desc: The length of the dithering or halftoning matrix used to create a dithered or halftoned bilevel file.

266.name: FillOrder
266.desc: The logical order of bits within a byte.

269.name: DocumentName
269.desc: The name of the document from which this image was scanned.

270.name: ImageDescription
270.desc: A string that describes the subject of the image.

272.name: Model
272.short_desc: The scanner model name or number.
272.desc: The scanner model name or number.

273.name: StripOffsets
273.desc: For each strip, the byte offset of that strip.

274.name: Orientation
274.desc: The orientation of the image with respect to the rows and columns.

277.name: SamplesPerPixel
277.desc: The number of components per pixel.

278.name: RowsPerStrip
278.desc: The number of rows per strip.

279.name: StripByteCounts
279.desc: For each strip, the number of bytes in the strip after compression.

282.name: XResolution
282.desc: The number of pixels per ResolutionUnit in the ImageWidth direction.

283.name: YResolution
283.desc: The number of pixels per ResolutionUnit in the ImageLength direction.

284.name: PlanarConfiguration
284.desc: How the components of each pixel are stored.

285.name: PageName
285.desc: The name of the page from which this image was scanned.

288.name: FreeOffsets
288.short_desc: For each string of contiguous unused bytes in a TIFF file, the byte offset of the string.
288.desc: For each string of contiguous unused bytes in a TIFF file, the byte offset of the string.

289.name: FreeByteCounts
289.short_desc: For each string of contiguous unused bytes in a TIFF file, the number of bytes in the string.
289.desc: For each string of contiguous unused bytes in a TIFF file, the number of bytes in the string.

290.name: GrayResponseUnit
290.desc: The precision of the information contained in the GrayResponseCurve.

291.name: GrayResponseCurve
291.desc: For grayscale data, the optical density of each possible pixel value.

296.name: ResolutionUnit
296.desc: The unit of measurement for XResolution and YResolution.

297.name: PageNumber
297.desc: The page number of the page from which this image was scanned.

301.name: TransferFunction
301.desc: Describes a transfer function for the image in tabular style.

305.name: Software
305.short_desc: Name and version number of the software package(s) used to create the image.
305.desc: Name and version number of the software package(s) used to create the image.

306.name: DateTime
306.desc: Date and time of image creation.

316.name: HostComputer
316.desc: The computer and/or operating system in use at the time of image creation.

317.name: Predictor
317.desc: A mathematical operator that is applied to the image data before an encoding scheme is applied.

318.name: WhitePoint
318.short_desc: The chromaticity of the white point of the image.
318.desc: The chromaticity of the white point of the image.

319.name: PrimaryChromaticities
319.desc: The chromaticities of the primaries of the image.

320.name: ColorMap
320.desc: A color map for palette color images.

321.name: HalftoneHints
321.desc: Conveys to the halftone function the range of gray levels within a colorimetrically-specified image that should retain tonal detail.

322.name: TileWidth
322.desc: The tile width in pixels. This is the number of columns in each tile.

323.name: TileLength
323.desc: The tile length (height) in pixels. This is the number of rows in each tile.

324.name: TileOffsets
324.desc: For each tile, the byte offset of that tile, as compressed and stored on disk.

325.name: TileByteCounts
325.desc: For each tile, the number of (compressed) bytes in that tile.

326.name: BadFaxLines
326.desc: Used in the TIFF-F standard, denotes the number of 'bad' scan lines encountered by the facsimile device.

327.name: CleanFaxData
327.desc: Used in the TIFF-F standard, indicates if 'bad' lines encountered during reception are stored in the data, or if 'bad' lines have been replaced by the receiver.

328.name: ConsecutiveBadFaxLines
328.desc: Used in the TIFF-F standard, denotes the maximum number of consecutive 'bad' scanlines received.

332.name: InkSet
332.desc: The set of inks used in a separated (PhotometricInterpretation=5) image.

333.name: InkNames
333.desc: The name of each ink used in a separated image.

336.name: DotRange
336.desc: The component values that correspond to a 0% dot and 100% dot.

337.name: TargetPrinter
337.desc: A description of the printing environment for which this separation is intended.

339.name: SampleFormat
339.desc: Specifies how to interpret each data sample in a pixel.

342.name: TransferRange
342.desc: Expands the range of the TransferFunction.

343.name: ClipPath
343.desc: Mirrors the essentials of PostScript's path creation functionality.

344.name: XClipPathUnits
344.desc: The number of units that span the width of the image, in terms of integer ClipPath coordinates.

345.name: YClipPathUnits
345.desc: The number of units that span the height of the image, in terms of integer ClipPath coordinates.

346.name: Indexed
346.desc: Aims to broaden the support for indexed images to include support for any color space.

400.name: GlobalParametersIFD
400.desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard to point to an IFD containing tags that are globally applicable to the complete TIFF file.

404.desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, denotes the year of the standard specified by the FaxProfile field.

405.name: ModeNumber
405.desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, denotes the mode of the standard specified by the FaxProfile field.
